=head1 DESCRIPTION

The API of the connector application that Amazon AppFlow uses to
transfer your data.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Name => Str

The name of the connector application API.


=head2 Type => Str

You can specify one of the following types:

=over

=item AUTOMATIC

The default. Optimizes a flow for datasets that fluctuate in size from
small to large. For each flow run, Amazon AppFlow chooses to use the
SYNC or ASYNC API type based on the amount of data that the run
transfers.

=item SYNC

A synchronous API. This type of API optimizes a flow for small to
medium-sized datasets.

=item ASYNC

An asynchronous API. This type of API optimizes a flow for large
datasets.

=back




